### ResultCrafter Demo — HTTP Requests
### Base URL: https://localhost:5001
### Run the demo project, then execute any request in your IDE.

@base = https://localhost:80/api

# ============================================================
# MINIMAL API ENDPOINTS  (/api/items/*)
# ============================================================

### [200] Get existing item — create one first via POST /items
GET {{base}}/items/1
Accept: application/json

###

### [404] Get item that does not exist
GET {{base}}/items/9999
Accept: application/json

###

### [201] Create item — valid request
POST {{base}}/items
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Widget Pro",
    "price": 29.99,
    "stock": 100
}

###

### [400] Create item — validation failure (field errors)
POST {{base}}/items
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "",
    "price": -5,
    "stock": 10
}

###

### [200] Update item — valid request (use version=1 after creating)
PUT {{base}}/items/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Widget Pro v2",
    "price": 34.99,
    "stock": 80,
    "version": 1
}

###

### [400] Update item — validation failure (field errors)
PUT {{base}}/items/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "",
    "price": 0,
    "stock": -10,
    "version": 1
}

###

### [409] Update item — concurrency conflict (stale version)
PUT {{base}}/items/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Widget Pro",
    "price": 29.99,
    "stock": 100,
    "version": 999
}

###

### [409] Update item — name conflict (same name as another item)
# First create a second item, then try to rename item 1 to match it
PUT {{base}}/items/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Existing Item Name",
    "price": 29.99,
    "stock": 100,
    "version": 2
}

###

### [204] Delete item
DELETE {{base}}/items/1
Accept: application/json

###

### [404] Delete item that does not exist
DELETE {{base}}/items/9999
Accept: application/json

###

### [202] Reserve item — background workflow queued, poll GET /items/{id} to confirm
POST {{base}}/items/1/reserve
Accept: application/json

###

### [403] Reserve item that is already reserved
POST {{base}}/items/1/reserve
Accept: application/json

###

### [404] Reserve item that does not exist
POST {{base}}/items/9999/reserve
Accept: application/json

###

### [202] Bulk delete — valid request (no response body)
POST {{base}}/items/bulk-delete
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "ids": [
        2,
        3,
        4
    ]
}

###

### [400] Bulk delete — empty list (plain detail, no errors dict)
POST {{base}}/items/bulk-delete
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "ids": []
}

###

### [400] Bulk delete — invalid IDs (structured errors dict)
POST {{base}}/items/bulk-delete
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "ids": [
        -1,
        0,
        5
    ]
}

###

### [200] Admin list — authenticated and authorized
GET {{base}}/items/admin
Accept: application/json
X-Api-Key: any-value-works
X-Role: admin

###

### [401] Admin list — missing API key
GET {{base}}/items/admin
Accept: application/json

###

### [403] Admin list — wrong role
GET {{base}}/items/admin
Accept: application/json
X-Api-Key: any-value-works
X-Role: viewer

###

### [500] Unhandled exception demo — ResultCrafterExceptionHandler converts to 500 ProblemDetails
# Watch the server logs: the full exception is logged at Error level.
# The response detail is sanitized in production, full in dev/staging.
GET {{base}}/items/crash
Accept: application/json

###

### [409] DbUpdateConcurrencyException demo — EfCore handler intercepts as 409
# The EfCoreConcurrencyExceptionHandler fires BEFORE the generic 500 handler.
# This demonstrates that DbUpdateConcurrencyException never becomes a 500.
GET {{base}}/items/db-crash
Accept: application/json

###


# ============================================================
# MVC CONTROLLER ENDPOINTS  (/api/ctrl/items/*)
# Same ItemService, same results — different routing + MVC syntax.
# ============================================================

@ctrl = https://localhost:5001/api/ctrl

### [200] Get existing item (controller)
GET {{ctrl}}/items/1
Accept: application/json

###

### [404] Get item that does not exist (controller)
GET {{ctrl}}/items/9999
Accept: application/json

###

### [201] Create item (controller)
POST {{ctrl}}/items
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Controller Widget",
    "price": 19.99,
    "stock": 50
}

###

### [400] Create item — validation failure (controller)
POST {{ctrl}}/items
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "",
    "price": -1,
    "stock": 10
}

###

### [200] Update item (controller)
PUT {{ctrl}}/items/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Controller Widget v2",
    "price": 24.99,
    "stock": 40,
    "version": 1
}

###

### [409] Update item — concurrency conflict (controller)
PUT {{ctrl}}/items/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Controller Widget",
    "price": 19.99,
    "stock": 50,
    "version": 999
}

###

### [204] Delete item (controller)
DELETE {{ctrl}}/items/1
Accept: application/json

###

### [202] Reserve item (controller)
POST {{ctrl}}/items/1/reserve
Accept: application/json

###

### [202] Bulk delete (controller)
POST {{ctrl}}/items/bulk-delete
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "ids": [
        10,
        11,
        12
    ]
}

###

### [400] Bulk delete — empty list (controller)
POST {{ctrl}}/items/bulk-delete
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "ids": []
}

###

### [200] Admin list (controller)
GET {{ctrl}}/items/admin
Accept: application/json
X-Api-Key: any-value-works
X-Role: admin

###

### [401] Admin list — missing API key (controller)
GET {{ctrl}}/items/admin
Accept: application/json

###

### [403] Admin list — wrong role (controller)
GET {{ctrl}}/items/admin
Accept: application/json
X-Api-Key: any-value-works
X-Role: viewer

###

### [500] Unhandled exception demo (controller) — same IExceptionHandler as Minimal API
GET {{ctrl}}/items/crash
Accept: application/json

###

### [409] DbUpdateConcurrencyException demo (controller) — same EfCore handler
GET {{ctrl}}/items/db-crash
Accept: application/json

###
